ygData.messageBody:
Whoa whoa whoa, if you're gonna Hunt Wisps, um, the island at Erud's Xing
has TONS of wisps, although I got a LOT of Burnt outs, I also got a few GLs
and several normals....But the wisps there are soooo much better than 1 ever
30 minutes...yikes, they're very abundant when the island isn't being
camped...but do NOT kill Kerra Beetles, whatever you do, and the spiders
WILL mob you, oh and the zombie sailors drop raw hide and coin...not a bad
place...
-----Original Message-----
From: Greg Jordon <greg@...>
To: EQ-Monks@onelist.com <EQ-Monks@onelist.com>
Date: Wednesday, August 25, 1999 3:54 PM
Subject: Re: [EQ-Monks] Hunting wisps


>From: "Greg Jordon" <greg@...>
>
>
>
> In my experience, there is a small set of valleys and high mountains
>slightly off to the right of the road when coming out of Surefall Glade, in
>the Queynos hills. If you want to hunt wisps, you may find 1 every thirty
>minutes or more around that area..... That is the most abundant spawn I
>know of... Although a ways away from your location... Just trying to
>help.
>
> --
>Dakkonan, level 8th monk, of Xegony.
